'''''Dnieper River Line''''' is a [[computer wargame]] published in 1982 by [[Avalon Hill|The Avalon Hill Game Company]].

==Gameplay==
''Dnieper River Line'' is a game in which the German defensive line of the [[Battle of the Dnieper]] is simulated.<ref name="CGW5"/>

==Reception==
Richard Charles Karr reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "''Dnieper River Line'' incorporates the elements of historical accuracy, as well as fast-paced situation-in-doubt play to produce a well developed game which computer wargamers should "check out"."<ref name="CGW5">{{cite magazine |last=Karr |first=Richard Charles |title=Dnieper River Line or "How Can You Be Two Places At Once When You're Not Anywhere At All?" |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=July–August 1982 |volume=1 |issue=5 |pages=28–29, 38}}</ref>

